# Gugugram Architecture Rules

- Keep strict layer flow: `actions -> services -> repositories -> external sources`.
- Do not skip layers (`actions` must not import repositories directly).
- Repositories contain only Drizzle queries and data access helpers.
- Services hold business rules (auth checks, ownership, sanitization, rate limits).
- Prefer path aliases from `tsconfig.json` (`@services/*`, `@repositories/*`, `@utils/*`, etc.).
- Respect `eslint-plugin-boundaries` constraints configured in `eslint.config.js`.

## Placement Conventions

- `src/actions/`: Astro server actions for input/auth/parsing and service orchestration.
- `src/services/`: business logic only.
- `src/repositories/`: DB access only.
- `src/pages/`: route handlers and page composition through services/components.
- `src/infra/`: external clients (`db`, upload/storage, integrations), no business logic.
